1
00:00:36,933 --> 00:00:39,133
<i>I'll put all my savings
into this because I trust you.</i>

2
00:00:39,267 --> 00:00:41,133
<i> Don't worry, this is legit.</i>

3
00:00:41,267 --> 00:00:42,900
<i> How are you guys doing at FMP?</i>

4
00:00:43,233 --> 00:00:44,967
<i>There are still online bashers.</i>

5
00:00:45,100 --> 00:00:49,533
<i>Those who believed Hazel's
exposé against Ma'am Felma.</i>

6
00:00:49,667 --> 00:00:51,067
<i>What are you planning to do
with these?</i>

7
00:00:51,200 --> 00:00:52,033
<i> What's that?</i>

8
00:00:52,167 --> 00:00:54,567
<i>This is a fact-acting laxative.</i>

9
00:00:54,700 --> 00:00:56,400
<i> Don't hesitate to come to me.</i>

10
00:00:56,533 --> 00:00:57,867
<i> We're family.</i>

11
00:00:58,000 --> 00:01:00,800
<i>- By the way, how is Jeff?
- He has already found a job.</i>

12
00:01:00,933 --> 00:01:01,900
<i> Excuse me.</i>

13
00:01:02,033 --> 00:01:04,333
<i>- Newbie?
- Let's see how long he lasts.</i>

14
00:01:04,467 --> 00:01:06,233
<i>Bet you anything, Jopet,
one week tops.</i>

15
00:01:06,367 --> 00:01:07,600
<i> This is for both of you.</i>

16
00:01:07,767 --> 00:01:08,833
<i> I love you.</i>

17
00:01:08,967 --> 00:01:10,500
<i> You poisoned us! You!</i>

18
00:01:10,633 --> 00:01:13,233
<i>Why are so many people
having diarrhea?</i>

19
00:01:13,367 --> 00:01:19,967
<i>Are you sure
your stomach pain</i>

20
00:01:20,100 --> 00:01:22,567
<i>was caused by the food
Miss Martinez served?</i>

21
00:01:22,700 --> 00:01:25,167
<i>- Yes, Ms. Chairwoman.
- Yes, Ma'am.</i>

22
00:01:25,300 --> 00:01:29,067
<i>"Sisig ni Bunso" is high
quality. It's made by FMP.</i>

23
00:01:29,200 --> 00:01:30,400
<i>- Hey!
- FMP.</i>

24
00:01:30,533 --> 00:01:31,767
<i> FMP!</i>

25
00:01:31,900 --> 00:01:34,600
<i>More than thirty people were
food poisoned from your sisig!</i>

26
00:01:34,733 --> 00:01:36,400
<i> I might get sued.</i>

27
00:01:36,533 --> 00:01:38,767
<i>Come out here!
Let the owner come out!</i>

28
00:01:40,567 --> 00:01:41,567
<i> My parcel!</i>

29
00:01:41,700 --> 00:01:43,000
<i> Mister, pull back!</i>

30
00:01:43,133 --> 00:01:44,833
<i> Pull back!</i>

31
00:01:44,967 --> 00:01:45,967
<i> It's broken.</i>

32
00:01:47,033 --> 00:01:48,333
<i> Hello, Daisy?</i>

33
00:01:48,467 --> 00:01:49,300
<i> What?</i>

34
00:01:49,433 --> 00:01:51,300
<i> What happened to my son?</i>

35
00:01:51,433 --> 00:01:53,333
The laptop cost
15,000 pesos,

36
00:01:53,467 --> 00:01:55,867
and the phone around
30,000 pesos.

37
00:01:56,000 --> 00:01:58,367
It's more expensive
because it's the latest model.

38
00:01:58,500 --> 00:02:00,733
Isn't it covered
by the insurance?

39
00:02:00,867 --> 00:02:02,767
It still needs
to be investigated.

40
00:02:02,900 --> 00:02:05,767
However, according to my boss,

41
00:02:05,900 --> 00:02:07,600
it seems impossible.

42
00:02:07,733 --> 00:02:10,267
It appears that this
was an operational incident.

43
00:02:10,400 --> 00:02:12,233
The items were mishandled.

44
00:02:12,367 --> 00:02:14,500
<i>So the company
might not cover it.</i>

45
00:02:14,667 --> 00:02:15,767
Bro, what about the motorcycle?

46
00:02:15,900 --> 00:02:17,433
<i>The money I used
for the down payment.</i>

47
00:02:17,567 --> 00:02:18,933
<i>You can worry about that later.</i>

48
00:02:19,067 --> 00:02:22,000
There's more bad news.

49
00:02:22,133 --> 00:02:23,433
<i> The boss said...</i>

50
00:02:23,567 --> 00:02:25,300
you're fired.

51
00:02:25,433 --> 00:02:26,467
<i> I'm sorry, Bro.</i>

52
00:02:28,667 --> 00:02:30,167
Bro?

53
00:02:30,300 --> 00:02:31,300
Hello.

54
00:02:39,700 --> 00:02:42,400
<i> Pull back!</i>

55
00:02:46,500 --> 00:02:48,267
<i> Check the other one, Bro.</i>

56
00:02:48,433 --> 00:02:49,633
<i> It's broken.</i>

57
00:02:53,767 --> 00:02:55,733
<i> The laptop cost 15,000 pesos,</i>

58
00:02:55,867 --> 00:02:58,167
<i>and the phone around
30,000 pesos.</i>

59
00:02:58,300 --> 00:03:00,367
<i>It's more expensive
because it's the latest model.</i>

60
00:03:04,233 --> 00:03:05,533
Jeff?

61
00:03:08,867 --> 00:03:09,767
Jeff?

62
00:03:10,933 --> 00:03:12,500
Where does it hurt?

63
00:03:12,633 --> 00:03:14,700
Do you want me to bring you
to the hospital?

64
00:03:17,667 --> 00:03:19,733
I was being careful, Daisy.

65
00:03:22,133 --> 00:03:23,667
I didn't even eat lunch.

66
00:03:25,300 --> 00:03:26,933
Because...

67
00:03:27,067 --> 00:03:29,000
I wanted to deliver
all the parcels.

68
00:03:30,400 --> 00:03:31,767
Because I wanted
to impress them.

69
00:03:31,900 --> 00:03:34,167
Because I wanted to be there
for the long run.

70
00:03:35,433 --> 00:03:37,667
I'm doing this for you
and Tetay.

71
00:03:38,767 --> 00:03:41,500
Because I want my daughter
to be proud of me.

72
00:03:43,800 --> 00:03:44,967
I don't even have
any money left.

73
00:03:45,100 --> 00:03:47,700
I just wanted to do that one
thing for my child, you know?

74
00:03:58,433 --> 00:04:00,500
It wasn't my fault.

75
00:04:00,633 --> 00:04:02,533
It was that driver's fault!

76
00:04:02,667 --> 00:04:03,867
What the heck!

77
00:04:04,000 --> 00:04:06,233
I always end up failing!

78
00:04:07,300 --> 00:04:10,100
I was careful so I could bring
something home for both of you.

79
00:04:11,467 --> 00:04:12,767
The laptop was broken.

80
00:04:12,900 --> 00:04:15,600
The cellphone was broken.

81
00:04:15,733 --> 00:04:18,000
How am I supposed to pay
for all that?

82
00:04:20,367 --> 00:04:21,667
I always end up failing!

83
00:04:21,800 --> 00:04:23,633
I'm always a failure!

84
00:04:34,667 --> 00:04:36,700
I haven't done
a single thing right!

85
00:04:39,533 --> 00:04:41,400
Every darn time!

86
00:04:43,767 --> 00:04:45,400
<i> 50,000 pesos?</i>

87
00:04:45,533 --> 00:04:47,800
Do I look like a bank to you?

88
00:04:48,800 --> 00:04:50,933
There's no one else
I can turn to for help.

89
00:04:51,067 --> 00:04:53,400
I'm broke, too.

90
00:04:53,533 --> 00:04:55,500
And out of all the jobs
you could've chosen,

91
00:04:55,633 --> 00:04:57,500
why become a rider?

92
00:04:57,633 --> 00:05:00,700
- You can just be a...
- Can you not lecture me?

93
00:05:00,867 --> 00:05:01,633
<i> Please.</i>

94
00:05:01,767 --> 00:05:03,533
And let me be, please.

95
00:05:04,867 --> 00:05:06,000
Just lend me some money.

96
00:05:06,133 --> 00:05:08,200
I promise to pay you back
as soon as things get better.

97
00:05:08,333 --> 00:05:11,200
I really don't have money, Jeff.

98
00:05:11,333 --> 00:05:12,933
Don't you have savings?

99
00:05:13,067 --> 00:05:17,467
I put down the advance
and deposit for the condo.

100
00:05:17,600 --> 00:05:22,033
Then I bought a new laptop
for the new job.

101
00:05:22,167 --> 00:05:25,300
I also invested
in a lending business.

102
00:05:25,433 --> 00:05:27,833
What? How much did you invest?

103
00:05:27,967 --> 00:05:30,300
150,000 pesos.

104
00:05:30,433 --> 00:05:32,467
Are you even thinking?

105
00:05:32,600 --> 00:05:34,733
<i> What if it's a scam?</i>

106
00:05:34,900 --> 00:05:37,800
You said to stay out
of your decisions.

107
00:05:37,933 --> 00:05:39,833
Then stay out of mine, too.

108
00:05:39,967 --> 00:05:42,300
Andrea, I thought we'd help
each other out?

109
00:05:42,433 --> 00:05:43,433
<i> Fine.</i>

110
00:05:43,567 --> 00:05:45,867
I still have 10,000 pesos
in the bank.

111
00:05:46,000 --> 00:05:47,000
That's all I have left.

112
00:05:47,133 --> 00:05:49,500
Is there anyone else
you could borrow money from?

113
00:05:50,567 --> 00:05:51,800
That person...

114
00:05:51,933 --> 00:05:52,833
Joel, right?

115
00:05:52,967 --> 00:05:54,033
Maybe you could borrow from him.

116
00:05:54,167 --> 00:05:55,700
<i> Come on, Jeff.</i>

117
00:05:55,833 --> 00:05:57,400
I hardly know the guy,

118
00:05:57,533 --> 00:05:59,267
and you expect me to borrow
from him right away?

119
00:05:59,400 --> 00:06:01,333
<i>As if I'm not going
to pay you back.</i>

120
00:06:01,467 --> 00:06:02,267
Can you really stand
not helping me?

121
00:06:02,400 --> 00:06:03,567
You're so stingy!

122
00:06:03,700 --> 00:06:04,967
I will pay you back!

123
00:06:05,100 --> 00:06:07,033
Wait a minute, Jeff.

124
00:06:07,200 --> 00:06:09,033
Let's not keep scores, okay?

125
00:06:10,300 --> 00:06:11,700
And why am I stingy?

126
00:06:12,633 --> 00:06:15,400
I'm willing
to give you 10,000 pesos.

127
00:06:15,533 --> 00:06:17,267
And that's my last money.

128
00:06:18,933 --> 00:06:20,267
Hello?

129
00:06:26,833 --> 00:06:27,567
<i> Anything, Bro.</i>

130
00:06:27,700 --> 00:06:29,900
I'll even go
for a '5-6' lending.

131
00:06:30,033 --> 00:06:30,567
<i> What?</i>

132
00:06:30,700 --> 00:06:32,233
Are you out of your mind?

133
00:06:32,367 --> 00:06:33,933
Are you really going to borrow
50,000 pesos through a '5-6'?

134
00:06:34,067 --> 00:06:36,067
<i>Do you have anything to use
as collateral?</i>

135
00:06:36,200 --> 00:06:37,133
The motorcycle, maybe.

136
00:06:37,267 --> 00:06:38,133
I was planning
to get it repaired.

137
00:06:38,267 --> 00:06:40,733
I'll use it as collateral.

138
00:06:40,900 --> 00:06:43,733
You'll only drown in debt.
I've been through that.

139
00:06:43,867 --> 00:06:46,200
<i>Fine, Bro, don't get mad. Okay?</i>

140
00:06:46,333 --> 00:06:48,167
I just have a suggestion.

141
00:06:48,300 --> 00:06:49,167
I know what you're about to say,

142
00:06:49,300 --> 00:06:50,600
and you already know
how I feel about it.

143
00:06:51,800 --> 00:06:52,767
No.

144
00:06:53,933 --> 00:06:55,100
I will never return to FMP.

145
00:06:55,233 --> 00:06:57,933
And I will never
ask for help from my mom.

146
00:06:58,067 --> 00:06:58,933
Jeff!

147
00:06:59,067 --> 00:07:01,767
Jeff! Jeff, what happened
to you?

148
00:07:01,900 --> 00:07:03,767
Son, let me bring you
to the hospital.

149
00:07:03,900 --> 00:07:05,167
Please, Son.

150
00:07:06,567 --> 00:07:07,433
Sorry, Jeff.

151
00:07:07,567 --> 00:07:09,267
I'm just worried about you.

152
00:07:09,400 --> 00:07:11,067
You need help.

153
00:07:17,700 --> 00:07:23,900
Miss Martinez, on behalf of FMP,
I apologize again.

154
00:07:25,700 --> 00:07:27,400
It's okay, Miss Antonio.

155
00:07:27,533 --> 00:07:30,500
Just make sure
I won't get involved.

156
00:07:30,633 --> 00:07:31,433
Wait.

157
00:07:31,567 --> 00:07:33,400
Why do we still sound so formal?

158
00:07:33,533 --> 00:07:34,800
Just call me Alice.

159
00:07:34,933 --> 00:07:37,833
We're friends anyway.

160
00:07:37,967 --> 00:07:38,867
Really?

161
00:07:39,000 --> 00:07:41,200
Do you really see me
as a friend?

162
00:07:41,333 --> 00:07:43,167
Gosh, you're so sweet.

163
00:07:44,833 --> 00:07:46,533
- Excuse me.
- Hi, Angge.

164
00:07:46,667 --> 00:07:50,800
Here's the public statement
that Atty. Yeban sent.

165
00:07:50,967 --> 00:07:52,333
Oh, okay.

166
00:07:53,967 --> 00:07:56,533
We are aware of the reports
linking our product

167
00:07:56,667 --> 00:08:00,400
to a possible food poisoning
incident.

168
00:08:00,533 --> 00:08:01,333
As a precaution,

169
00:08:01,467 --> 00:08:03,767
we are initiating
a voluntary recall

170
00:08:03,900 --> 00:08:05,100
of a specific batch of...

171
00:08:05,233 --> 00:08:08,333
FMP remains committed
to high standards...

172
00:08:08,467 --> 00:08:09,367
Thank you.

173
00:08:09,500 --> 00:08:10,733
This is okay.

174
00:08:10,867 --> 00:08:11,700
This is okay for me.

175
00:08:11,833 --> 00:08:14,433
But send a copy first
to Miss Felma.

176
00:08:14,567 --> 00:08:16,333
She might have more to add.

177
00:08:16,467 --> 00:08:17,300
- Okay, I will.
- Okay.

178
00:08:17,433 --> 00:08:19,300
- Thank you.
- Thanks, Angge.

179
00:08:21,200 --> 00:08:23,100
I'll get going, Paz.

180
00:08:23,233 --> 00:08:25,567
Looks like you still have a lot
to take care of.

181
00:08:25,700 --> 00:08:27,233
Thank you, Alice.

182
00:08:27,367 --> 00:08:31,600
I hope you don't pull out
as our distributor.

183
00:08:31,733 --> 00:08:32,667
No, never.

184
00:08:32,800 --> 00:08:36,367
I still trust FMP,
and it will never change.

185
00:08:36,500 --> 00:08:39,300
Oh, you are really so sweet.
You're so touching.

186
00:08:39,433 --> 00:08:41,667
Come here! I'll touch you.

187
00:08:44,167 --> 00:08:46,400
<i> - You're so sweet.
-</i> Thank you.

188
00:08:46,533 --> 00:08:47,800
Where's Paz?

189
00:08:49,267 --> 00:08:50,067
Thank you.

190
00:08:50,200 --> 00:08:51,900
Ling?

191
00:08:52,033 --> 00:08:53,467
- Just keep on fighting.
- Fighting, right?

192
00:08:53,600 --> 00:08:54,400
Super.

193
00:08:54,567 --> 00:08:56,067
- Thank you.
- Really.

194
00:09:00,033 --> 00:09:01,600
Thank you, I mean it.

195
00:09:01,733 --> 00:09:04,067
Thank you so much, too.

196
00:09:11,467 --> 00:09:12,433
Get out of here.

197
00:09:13,400 --> 00:09:15,833
I don't need you.
Get out of here now!

198
00:09:15,967 --> 00:09:19,100
- Jeff, listen to me.
- I said, I don't need you!

199
00:09:19,233 --> 00:09:20,267
Jeff,

200
00:09:20,400 --> 00:09:22,600
don't yell at Aunt Felma!

201
00:09:22,733 --> 00:09:25,167
Good thing your daughter
is at our neighbor's place.

202
00:09:25,300 --> 00:09:27,500
I don't want her to see
how you treat your mother.

203
00:09:27,667 --> 00:09:30,167
Because she might
do the same thing to me!

204
00:09:30,300 --> 00:09:31,967
Daisy, I hate being rude
to my mom!

205
00:09:33,000 --> 00:09:35,033
But you're pushing me
to my limits!

206
00:09:35,167 --> 00:09:37,767
Why did you tell her?
To humiliate me?

207
00:09:37,900 --> 00:09:39,567
She's your mom.

208
00:09:39,700 --> 00:09:40,367
It's not wrong

209
00:09:40,500 --> 00:09:42,100
- to let her know...
- What?

210
00:09:42,233 --> 00:09:43,700
That his son is a failure?

211
00:09:43,833 --> 00:09:45,500
That he keeps making mistakes?

212
00:09:46,600 --> 00:09:47,900
And he can't support his family?

213
00:09:48,033 --> 00:09:49,600
Is that what you want
her to see?

214
00:09:49,733 --> 00:09:50,800
No!

215
00:09:50,933 --> 00:09:52,467
I want her to know
that you need help.

216
00:09:52,600 --> 00:09:53,500
And that you're having
a hard time,

217
00:09:53,633 --> 00:09:55,967
no matter how you try.

218
00:09:56,933 --> 00:09:59,200
You need a mom
who will help you.

219
00:10:00,467 --> 00:10:03,533
And will encourage you, Son.

220
00:10:03,700 --> 00:10:05,533
Son, please
don't be so difficult.

221
00:10:07,367 --> 00:10:11,300
- Let your mom help you.
- I said I don't need you!

222
00:10:12,833 --> 00:10:14,633
Go and be with your new family.

223
00:10:16,633 --> 00:10:17,800
Mom...

224
00:10:17,933 --> 00:10:20,533
you chose them, didn't you?
That man and his daughter.

225
00:10:20,667 --> 00:10:22,500
You chose them.

226
00:10:22,633 --> 00:10:23,600
Not us.

227
00:10:25,267 --> 00:10:26,667
That's not true.

228
00:10:26,800 --> 00:10:28,167
What do you mean, not true?

229
00:10:30,433 --> 00:10:32,233
Who's inside the house?

230
00:10:33,900 --> 00:10:35,467
And who's outside?

231
00:10:38,867 --> 00:10:42,000
Andrea and I no longer have
a place in your world.

232
00:10:44,000 --> 00:10:45,400
None.

233
00:10:51,000 --> 00:10:52,033
Son!

234
00:10:52,900 --> 00:10:54,367
Jeff!

235
00:10:54,500 --> 00:10:55,567
Jeff!

236
00:11:09,833 --> 00:11:11,500
That's not true!

237
00:11:12,600 --> 00:11:14,600
That's not true.

238
00:11:27,067 --> 00:11:28,233
Auntie!

239
00:11:29,467 --> 00:11:30,933
Where are you going?

240
00:11:31,067 --> 00:11:32,433
We were planning to go to FMP.

241
00:11:32,567 --> 00:11:35,833
We wanted to bring food to you
and your staff.

242
00:11:35,967 --> 00:11:38,233
Felma said you'd come home late

243
00:11:38,367 --> 00:11:40,233
because of the food poisoning
incident.

244
00:11:41,367 --> 00:11:43,833
We wanted to show our support.

245
00:11:43,967 --> 00:11:46,533
We're worried, Auntie.

246
00:11:46,667 --> 00:11:48,967
But, Auntie, why are you here?

247
00:11:49,100 --> 00:11:53,067
Value More
and Consumer Mart called.

248
00:11:53,200 --> 00:11:56,833
They're asking something
that I don't know the answer to.

249
00:11:56,967 --> 00:11:59,900
Only Felma can answer that.
But I couldn't reach Felma.

250
00:12:00,033 --> 00:12:01,867
So I rushed here.

251
00:12:04,833 --> 00:12:07,167
Mom hasn't gone home yet.

252
00:12:08,367 --> 00:12:10,300
Maybe something bad
has happened to her.

253
00:12:10,433 --> 00:12:12,167
Coleen, calm down.

254
00:12:12,300 --> 00:12:13,667
She's at Daisy's place.

255
00:12:13,800 --> 00:12:16,233
Because Jeff had an accident.

256
00:12:16,400 --> 00:12:18,033
What happened to my firstborn?

257
00:12:18,167 --> 00:12:18,867
Nothing.

258
00:12:19,000 --> 00:12:19,967
Manuel, sorry.

259
00:12:20,100 --> 00:12:22,800
He's okay. Just relax.

260
00:12:22,933 --> 00:12:26,600
Felma went there
to offer some help.

261
00:12:26,733 --> 00:12:28,633
Calm down. He's okay.

262
00:12:29,700 --> 00:12:32,033
And please be quiet.

263
00:12:32,167 --> 00:12:34,433
Felma doesn't want you to know.

264
00:12:42,267 --> 00:12:44,067
I'm not choosing anyone.

265
00:12:49,433 --> 00:12:51,300
I only want...

266
00:12:52,400 --> 00:12:55,867
Jeff and Andrea
to forgive their father.

267
00:13:01,833 --> 00:13:04,100
Manuel is regretful anyway.

268
00:13:07,700 --> 00:13:08,833
I know...

269
00:13:10,600 --> 00:13:13,433
I know that my firstborn
is mad at me.

270
00:13:16,267 --> 00:13:17,667
But I hope...

271
00:13:20,467 --> 00:13:22,400
I hope he doesn't think...

272
00:13:25,500 --> 00:13:28,933
that they have no place
in my world.

273
00:13:29,067 --> 00:13:31,167
Because that will never happen.

274
00:13:32,767 --> 00:13:35,367
That will never happen.

275
00:13:37,500 --> 00:13:40,167
Whatever storms we face,

276
00:13:41,400 --> 00:13:45,000
my love as their mother
will remain unbroken.

277
00:13:54,800 --> 00:13:56,233
But them?

278
00:13:57,467 --> 00:14:00,667
They can bear to stay mad at me.

279
00:14:04,967 --> 00:14:08,067
I miss you both so much,
my children.

280
00:14:09,933 --> 00:14:11,533
<i> Why is she still here?</i>

281
00:14:16,100 --> 00:14:18,000
Especially you, Jeff.

282
00:14:19,533 --> 00:14:21,900
You're my strength, Jeff.

283
00:14:24,200 --> 00:14:29,267
I'm this strong because of you.

284
00:14:31,633 --> 00:14:35,000
Because of how you protected me,

285
00:14:35,900 --> 00:14:38,100
because of your love.

286
00:14:48,467 --> 00:14:51,067
<i> You did everything for me.</i>

287
00:14:53,233 --> 00:14:55,967
<i>Even if you almost
risked your life.</i>

288
00:14:56,100 --> 00:14:58,900
<i>We will be turning your child
over to the DSWD.</i>

289
00:14:59,033 --> 00:15:00,433
<i>You'll take my son away from me?</i>

290
00:15:00,567 --> 00:15:02,233
<i> Mom, I don't want to.</i>

291
00:15:02,400 --> 00:15:04,233
<i> Don't let them do that.</i>

292
00:15:04,367 --> 00:15:08,267
<i>Mom, I don't want
to be away from you.</i>

293
00:15:08,400 --> 00:15:11,833
Because you didn't want us
to be apart.

294
00:15:16,400 --> 00:15:20,333
Jeff, my son.

295
00:15:20,467 --> 00:15:23,133
Let me be your strength
this time.

296
00:15:25,133 --> 00:15:29,200
Let me protect you this time,
Son.

297
00:15:29,933 --> 00:15:32,800
I'm right here.

298
00:15:48,933 --> 00:15:49,867
Jeff?

299
00:15:51,067 --> 00:15:52,100
Son.

300
00:15:59,000 --> 00:16:00,400
Mom, I'm sorry.

301
00:16:03,567 --> 00:16:04,733
I failed.

302
00:16:06,133 --> 00:16:08,167
I failed again, Mom.

303
00:16:12,000 --> 00:16:13,767
I always fail.

304
00:16:14,733 --> 00:16:18,233
Mom, I'm sorry. I thought
I could make it on my own.

305
00:16:18,367 --> 00:16:21,400
- I was wrong.
- Son.

306
00:16:21,533 --> 00:16:23,567
- Son...
- Sorry, Mom.

307
00:16:24,633 --> 00:16:27,767
I thought I could do it.

308
00:16:27,900 --> 00:16:30,233
- Son.
- I'm sorry.

309
00:16:30,367 --> 00:16:31,800
Son.

310
00:16:38,733 --> 00:16:41,367
Mom, I really tried. I promise.

311
00:16:41,500 --> 00:16:44,133
But your son is weakling.

312
00:16:44,300 --> 00:16:45,433
Weakling.

313
00:16:45,567 --> 00:16:47,400
Weakling.

314
00:16:47,533 --> 00:16:49,367
That's enough.

315
00:16:49,500 --> 00:16:50,667
Don't say that.

316
00:16:50,800 --> 00:16:52,600
Don't say that.

317
00:16:52,733 --> 00:16:55,067
My firstborn isn't a weakling.

318
00:16:55,200 --> 00:16:57,367
- Remember that.
- Sorry.

319
00:16:57,500 --> 00:16:58,867
That's not true.

320
00:17:00,300 --> 00:17:01,500
Son...

321
00:17:02,700 --> 00:17:04,867
Son, you're not a failure.

322
00:17:05,000 --> 00:17:07,233
You're never a failure, Son.

323
00:17:07,367 --> 00:17:09,733
You just got unlucky.

324
00:17:09,867 --> 00:17:12,367
But remember, I'm right here.

325
00:17:12,500 --> 00:17:14,333
I'll help you.

326
00:17:20,833 --> 00:17:23,267
Jeff, answer the call.

327
00:17:30,333 --> 00:17:32,200
Why are you even calling
your brother?

328
00:17:33,833 --> 00:17:35,367
You can't help him anyway.

329
00:17:36,567 --> 00:17:38,600
I'm going to help him.

330
00:17:38,733 --> 00:17:41,100
But not the entire 50,000 pesos.

331
00:17:41,233 --> 00:17:43,400
I'll lend him 10,000 pesos.

332
00:17:43,533 --> 00:17:46,333
And then he can figure out
where to get the rest of it.

333
00:17:46,467 --> 00:17:49,100
Andrea, I have money.

334
00:17:49,267 --> 00:17:50,667
I can lend him some.

335
00:17:59,700 --> 00:18:02,400
Joel, thanks for the offer.

336
00:18:03,633 --> 00:18:07,333
But I want my brother to learn
how to be responsible.

337
00:18:08,900 --> 00:18:13,400
He can't always come to us
whenever he has problems,

338
00:18:13,533 --> 00:18:15,000
then everything will
be alright for him.

339
00:18:17,133 --> 00:18:18,933
This is mom's fault.

340
00:18:19,067 --> 00:18:20,367
He was raised like that
because of her.

341
00:18:20,500 --> 00:18:22,500
He was raised spoiled.

342
00:18:22,667 --> 00:18:24,767
You're blaming
your mother again.

343
00:18:26,267 --> 00:18:27,400
Don't you know?

344
00:18:29,767 --> 00:18:30,833
Know what?

345
00:18:36,733 --> 00:18:37,900
<i> FMP!</i>

346
00:18:38,033 --> 00:18:40,433
<i> You scoundrels!</i>

347
00:18:40,567 --> 00:18:44,200
<i>More than thirty people were
food poisoned from your sisig!</i>

348
00:18:44,333 --> 00:18:45,500
<i> Fellow citizens,</i>

349
00:18:45,633 --> 00:18:50,267
<i>don't ever buy "Sisig ni Bunso"
made by FMP!</i>

350
00:18:50,400 --> 00:18:52,333
<i>- Yes!
- That's right!</i>

351
00:18:52,467 --> 00:18:56,100
<i>You might get food poisoned,
too, like us!</i>

352
00:19:05,900 --> 00:19:06,533
Mom?

353
00:19:07,533 --> 00:19:09,233
Felma, how's Jeffrey?

354
00:19:14,067 --> 00:19:15,433
How did you know?

355
00:19:20,533 --> 00:19:22,733
Sis, sorry.

356
00:19:22,867 --> 00:19:24,700
It slipped my tongue.

357
00:19:25,633 --> 00:19:28,800
Sis, what did my godson say?

358
00:19:28,967 --> 00:19:30,800
Did he accept your help?

359
00:19:32,400 --> 00:19:33,333
Yes.

360
00:19:34,567 --> 00:19:36,033
Looks like we're okay now.

361
00:19:36,167 --> 00:19:37,300
Really, Mom?

362
00:19:37,433 --> 00:19:40,300
That's great news, Auntie.

363
00:19:40,433 --> 00:19:42,267
Why didn't he come with you?

364
00:19:45,600 --> 00:19:47,467
He's not ready yet.

365
00:19:47,600 --> 00:19:49,333
Let's leave him be for now.

366
00:19:49,467 --> 00:19:52,100
At least, we're open
with each other now.

367
00:19:54,367 --> 00:19:56,100
But he's still mad at me.

368
00:19:56,233 --> 00:19:59,800
Manuel, let's not rush them.

369
00:19:59,933 --> 00:20:01,167
We'll get there someday.

370
00:20:01,300 --> 00:20:03,600
Your kids will
forgive you, too.

371
00:20:03,767 --> 00:20:06,000
Yes, Dad. Just be patient.

372
00:20:42,767 --> 00:20:44,200
- Hi.
- Hi.

373
00:20:44,333 --> 00:20:45,500
Good morning...

374
00:20:47,900 --> 00:20:50,733
Friend, why do you look
so haggard?

375
00:20:50,867 --> 00:20:53,300
Is it stressful at Southcrest?

376
00:20:54,467 --> 00:20:56,000
Yes.

377
00:20:56,133 --> 00:20:57,767
Super.

378
00:20:57,900 --> 00:20:59,533
But you know what?

379
00:20:59,667 --> 00:21:01,233
I enjoy it.

380
00:21:01,367 --> 00:21:02,967
I missed the...

381
00:21:03,100 --> 00:21:05,333
Filipino patients.

382
00:21:08,000 --> 00:21:10,300
Here, have some coffee.

383
00:21:10,433 --> 00:21:12,367
Is there an available position?

384
00:21:12,500 --> 00:21:14,000
I also want to apply.

385
00:21:14,133 --> 00:21:15,633
Oh, don't.

386
00:21:15,767 --> 00:21:17,700
I still need you
at Felma's office.

387
00:21:17,833 --> 00:21:20,933
Oh, come on.
I can handle both...

388
00:21:21,067 --> 00:21:23,267
<i>The office of Felma's Food
Products,</i>

389
00:21:23,400 --> 00:21:25,100
<i>which was visited earlier
by officials</i>

390
00:21:25,233 --> 00:21:28,000
<i>from the City Public
and Sanitation Office.</i>

391
00:21:28,133 --> 00:21:32,433
We are with Miss Felma,
CEO of FMP.

392
00:21:32,567 --> 00:21:35,467
Ma'am, can we get
your statement now?

393
00:21:35,600 --> 00:21:36,433
Yes.

394
00:21:36,567 --> 00:21:40,267
We're fully cooperating
with CPHSO.

395
00:21:40,400 --> 00:21:41,267
And within our company,

396
00:21:41,400 --> 00:21:44,067
we've been taking steps
since yesterday.

397
00:21:44,233 --> 00:21:47,933
To find out the whole truth
behind what happened.

398
00:21:48,067 --> 00:21:50,367
We've also coordinated
with everyone

399
00:21:50,500 --> 00:21:52,500
who suffered
from food poisoning.

400
00:21:52,633 --> 00:21:53,933
Thank you so much, Ma'am.

401
00:21:54,067 --> 00:21:55,800
Thank you so much, too.

402
00:22:04,533 --> 00:22:06,033
Won't you go to her?

403
00:22:10,967 --> 00:22:12,667
Hello, Attorney?

404
00:22:12,800 --> 00:22:13,567
Yes.

405
00:22:13,700 --> 00:22:14,433
Yes.

406
00:22:14,567 --> 00:22:17,400
The closure order
has been served.

407
00:22:17,567 --> 00:22:19,567
Yes, let's meet
at the City Hall.

408
00:22:19,700 --> 00:22:21,400
Thank you so much, Attorney.

409
00:22:44,667 --> 00:22:46,000
Look at that.

410
00:22:46,133 --> 00:22:49,167
Today is such a great day!

411
00:22:50,700 --> 00:22:51,767
Look at that.

412
00:22:51,900 --> 00:22:58,433
I can now sleep in peace
while FMP rests in pieces.

413
00:23:05,867 --> 00:23:09,500
Thank you for reaching out
so fast, Ms. Ruiz.

414
00:23:09,633 --> 00:23:13,533
We were able to contact
the victims of food poisoning.

415
00:23:13,667 --> 00:23:15,833
Thank you so much, too,
Ms. Chairwoman.

416
00:23:15,967 --> 00:23:18,500
We've already visited
ten of them.

417
00:23:18,633 --> 00:23:20,533
I've talked to them in person.

418
00:23:21,500 --> 00:23:23,500
I'm glad no one
was rushed to the hospital.

419
00:23:23,667 --> 00:23:25,900
And they're all safe.

420
00:23:26,033 --> 00:23:28,367
We...

421
00:23:28,500 --> 00:23:30,867
we just have a request,
Ms. Chairwoman.

422
00:23:32,800 --> 00:23:34,533
What is it?

423
00:23:38,933 --> 00:23:40,167
Ms. Chairwoman,

424
00:23:40,300 --> 00:23:42,700
we suspect that what happened
might have been intentional.

425
00:23:43,833 --> 00:23:46,667
Someone sabotaged us.

426
00:23:46,800 --> 00:23:52,067
If you have CCTV footage
of what happened yesterday,

427
00:23:52,200 --> 00:23:54,400
can we have a copy of it?

428
00:23:54,533 --> 00:23:56,767
To help with our investigation.

429
00:23:57,800 --> 00:24:00,033
I'm sorry, Ms. Ruiz.

430
00:24:00,167 --> 00:24:03,800
Our CCTVs aren't installed yet.

431
00:24:03,933 --> 00:24:05,067
But...

432
00:24:06,200 --> 00:24:09,833
I asked my staff
to record what happened.

433
00:24:09,967 --> 00:24:11,633
For documentation.

434
00:24:11,767 --> 00:24:14,767
Well, it's not
a full documentation,

435
00:24:14,900 --> 00:24:18,167
but it might help you.

436
00:24:22,867 --> 00:24:24,500
Sis.

437
00:24:24,633 --> 00:24:26,400
Sis, I know this man.

438
00:24:30,100 --> 00:24:30,900
<i>- Who are you?
- Jeffrey!</i>

439
00:24:31,033 --> 00:24:32,333
<i> Who are you?</i>

440
00:24:32,467 --> 00:24:35,033
<i>What are you doing
in my girlfriend's house?</i>

441
00:24:35,167 --> 00:24:37,733
<i> You're the thief!</i>

442
00:24:37,867 --> 00:24:39,500
<i>That explains
why you look familiar!</i>

443
00:24:39,633 --> 00:24:41,000
<i> My God, Hazel!</i>

444
00:24:41,133 --> 00:24:42,833
<i> Is he your henchman?</i>

445
00:24:42,967 --> 00:24:44,700
<i>Did you order him
to intrude on our house?</i>

446
00:24:44,833 --> 00:24:47,467
<i>Yes, that's him!
He's the one Jeffrey caught!</i>

447
00:24:47,600 --> 00:24:49,633
<i>Hey! What are you talking about?</i>

448
00:24:49,767 --> 00:24:51,067
<i> He's a police officer!</i>

449
00:24:51,200 --> 00:24:51,900
<i> He's a cop!</i>

450
00:24:52,033 --> 00:24:53,433
<i> I brought him as backup.</i>

451
00:24:53,567 --> 00:24:55,367
<i>So you'd bring my husband
and daughter out!</i>

452
00:24:55,500 --> 00:24:56,900
Sis,

453
00:24:57,033 --> 00:24:58,900
that's Alice Martinez.

454
00:24:59,033 --> 00:25:01,900
I knew it!
I knew it, that's her!

455
00:25:02,067 --> 00:25:04,000
That lowlife
has something to do with this!

456
00:25:04,133 --> 00:25:06,433
That Hazel! My gosh!

457
00:25:09,667 --> 00:25:10,800
Sis,

458
00:25:10,933 --> 00:25:13,433
did you see how that man

459
00:25:13,567 --> 00:25:15,300
and Miss Martinez
look at each other?

460
00:25:16,900 --> 00:25:20,400
Is she working with Hazel
as well?

461
00:25:28,500 --> 00:25:31,433
It's confirmed, Sis. Look!

462
00:25:31,567 --> 00:25:32,500
They're together.

463
00:25:32,633 --> 00:25:35,133
Alice is Hazel's puppet.

464
00:25:35,300 --> 00:25:40,367
Felma, may I see Jessica
before I go?

465
00:25:40,500 --> 00:25:44,467
Sure. I'll tell the guardhouse
to let you in.

466
00:25:44,600 --> 00:25:47,333
- I'll ask mom to ask if...
- To ask what?

467
00:25:47,467 --> 00:25:48,800
Aren't you still convinced?

468
00:25:48,933 --> 00:25:51,367
You saw that she has
worked with your godmother.

469
00:25:51,500 --> 00:25:52,267
But Coleen...

470
00:25:52,400 --> 00:25:54,700
Jessica, you won't tell your mom

471
00:25:54,833 --> 00:25:56,833
that my mom has found out
about her demon-like deeds.

472
00:25:56,967 --> 00:26:00,133
If you do that,
I'll be angrier at you!

473
00:26:00,267 --> 00:26:02,333
Call that Alice Martinez.

474
00:26:02,467 --> 00:26:06,933
Are we proceeding with the plan
for those twin elves?

475
00:26:07,067 --> 00:26:08,933
What is this emergency meeting
about?

476
00:26:09,100 --> 00:26:11,433
Is FMP back in business?

477
00:26:11,567 --> 00:26:14,367
You traitor,
you lowlife little goblin!

478
00:26:16,033 --> 00:26:18,033
Thank you so much.
